# .gitignore
# Tells Git which files and folders to NEVER upload to GitHub.
# These are either generated automatically (no need to store them),
# environment-specific (different on every machine), or sensitive
# (API keys, passwords — never put these on GitHub).

# ── Python cache files ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Python creates these automatically when it runs your code.
# They speed up imports locally but are machine-specific.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
*.pyd
.Python

# ── Virtual environment ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Your .venv folder contains all installed packages for your machine.
# Railway installs its own packages from requirements.txt — it doesn't
# need yours. Uploading .venv would add hundreds of MB to your repo.
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# ── Environment variables ───────────────────────────────────────
# If you ever create a .env file with API keys or secrets, this
# line ensures they never accidentally get pushed to GitHub.
.env
.env.*

# ── macOS system files ──────────────────────────────────────────
# macOS creates .DS_Store files in every folder automatically.
# They're invisible but clutter your repo with junk.
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# ── Test output and logs ────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.pot

# ── Distribution / packaging ────────────────────────────────────
# Generated if you ever try to package this as a Python library.
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
